Sentencas: The double-perovskite Sr2NiMoO6-delta (SNMO) was investigated as an anode material of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Sr2NiMoO6-δ as anode material for LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: With a 300 mu m thick La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-sigma (LSGM) disk as electrolyte and Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta as the cathode, the SNMO anode showed power densities of 819 mW cm(-2) in hydrogen at 1123 K.
Titulo: Sr2NiMoO6-δ as anode material for LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Moreover, there was no buffer layer between anode and electrolyte, which would reduce design techniques and save design cost.
Titulo: Sr2NiMoO6-δ as anode material for LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: After test no chemical reaction was discovered between anode and electrolyte.
Titulo: Sr2NiMoO6-δ as anode material for LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The anode exhibited good conductivity and the value was around 60 S cm(-1) in H-2.
Titulo: Sr2NiMoO6-δ as anode material for LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Also it had almost linear thermal expansion from room temperature to 1253 K and the average thermal expansion coefficient was about 12.14 x 10(-6) K-1, which was quite close to that of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (12.17 x 10(-6) K-1) electrolyte.
Titulo: Sr2NiMoO6-δ as anode material for LaGaO3-based solid oxide fuel cell
